      <h2 id="project-name">Project Name</h2>
      <p>
        Riordan Human Resource (HR) System – COTS Implementation
      </p>

      <h2 id="project-desc">Project Description</h2>
      <p>Riordan Manufacturing is a global plastics manufacturer that employs 550 people and projected annual earnings of $46 million. Riordan Manufacturing’s internal systems have been undergoing modernization efforts and the next phase is to combining
        and automating all of Riordan’s HR systems. Smith Consulting Services for (SR-RM-022) performed the business analysis of the organization’s HR system requirements and selected a COTS based HR solution. The scope of this project is to implement
        the selected HR solution.</p>

      <p>The overall goal of the project is to replace the organization’s multiple automated and manual human resource related processes with a single unified system.</p>

      <p>The project objectives include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Vendor contract</li>
        <li>Data migration</li>
        <li>System integration</li>
        <li>User acceptance testing</li>
        <li>Training</li>
        <li>System implementation</li>
      </ul>

      <p>The desired outcome of the project is to transition the organization effectively onto the new consolidated HR system.</p>

