      <h2 id="mov">Measurable Organizational Value (MOV)</h2>

      <p>Business Need/Problem 1: Riordan currently has multiple HR systems and processes used within the organization. This duplication of data and functionality is a source of many operational inefficiencies within the organization.</p>

      <p>Objective 1.1: Combine the multiple HR systems and processes into a single unified system. </p>
      <p>Measurement 1.1.1: A reduction in duplicated HR related data within the organization. </p>
      <p>Measurement 1.1.2: A reduction in the time necessary to complete HR related processes.</p>
      <p>Anticipated Benefit(s): Reduced duplication of effort and data, Increase in organizational process efficiency</p>


      <h2 id="roi">Project Return on Investment (ROI)</h2>
      <p>The organization projects an annual operational saving of $275,000 a year post implementation. The source of these saves stem from the elimination of individually licensed and supported HR systems within the organization. In addition, the organization
        estimates that the new system will reduce the resource costs associated with performing HR related processes by $50,000 annually. At this rate, the project costs will be recovered within 4 years after implementation.</p>

